Nersa approves 18.65% Eskom tariff increase.  JOHANNESBURG - Energy regulator Nersa has granted Eskom an 18.65% tariff increase for the 2023/24 financial year. This will kick in from April this year for Eskom's direct customers. WATCH | Nersa announcement on power price hike From April 2024, a 12.7% increase will kick in. Cash-strapped consumers will be paying an extra R1.73 per kilowatt hour for electricity. The latest tariff hike comes as Eskom is implementing record rolling blackouts.  #eNCA speaks to energy analyst Chris Yelland following the 18.65% electricity price hike announced by Nersa for the next financial year. #DStv403